  <!-- ========== FAQ ========== -->
  <section class="faq section--soft" id="faq">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="faq__layout">
        <div class="faq__left">
          <h2>Frequently Asked<br>Questions</h2>
          <p class="subheadline">Everything you need to know before we get started.</p>
          <a href="#contact" class="btn">Still Have Questions? Let's Talk</a>

          <div class="faq__authority">
            <div class="faq__authority-item">
              <span class="faq__authority-num">100's</span>
              <span class="faq__authority-label">Websites Launched</span>
            </div>
            <div class="faq__authority-item">
              <span class="faq__authority-num">25+</span>
              <span class="faq__authority-label">Industries Served</span>
            </div>
            <div class="faq__authority-item">
              <span class="faq__authority-num">5.0</span>
              <span class="faq__authority-label">Google Rating</span>
            </div>
            <div class="faq__authority-item">
              <span class="faq__authority-num">100%</span>
              <span class="faq__authority-label">Satisfaction Guarantee</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq__right">
          <div class="faq__group">
            <h3 class="faq__group-title">Investment & Value</h3>
            <details class="faq__item">
              <summary class="faq__question">What is the typical cost range for a lead-generating website for a service business?</summary>
              <div class="faq__answer"><p>A professionally built, lead-generating website for a service business typically costs between $5,000 and $25,000. The final investment depends on the project's scope — number of custom-designed pages, complexity of features (like online booking or cost calculators), and the depth of the SEO and content strategy. For example, a 10-page website for a local contractor with foundational SEO will be closer to the $5,000–$8,000 range, while a 25-page site for a multi-location firm with a comprehensive content strategy could be $15,000 or more. We provide a detailed, fixed-price proposal after our initial discovery call.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details class="faq__item">
              <summary class="faq__question">What specific deliverables are included in a standard website design package?</summary>
              <div class="faq__answer"><p>A standard website design package from Lockard Design Co. is a complete growth system that includes: custom strategy and design tailored to your brand and ideal customer (not a generic template), professional SEO-optimized copywriting written to convert visitors into leads, full technical SEO setup including sitemaps, schema markup, and Google Analytics, strategically placed lead capture forms integrated with your CRM, mobile-first responsive development, and post-launch training with a video walkthrough.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details class="faq__item">
              <summary class="faq__question">Are payment plans available for web design projects?</summary>
              <div class="faq__answer"><p>Yes, we offer flexible payment options. Our standard structure is a 50% deposit to secure your spot in our project calendar and 50% upon completion before the site goes live. For larger projects exceeding $15,000, we can arrange a milestone-based plan — typically 40% deposit, 30% at design approval, and 30% at launch.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details class="faq__item">
              <summary class="faq__question">How does a custom website's ROI compare to using a DIY website builder like Wix or Squarespace?</summary>
              <div class="faq__answer"><p>A custom website delivers a significantly higher return on investment than a DIY builder by focusing on lead generation and conversion, not just aesthetics. While DIY platforms have a lower upfront cost, they often result in a 'digital business card' that generates little to no traffic or leads. Our clients typically see a positive ROI within the first 12–18 months, as the website becomes a reliable source of qualified customer inquiries. The key difference is strategy — we build a system engineered to attract your ideal customer and guide them to a sale.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details class="faq__item">
              <summary class="faq__question">What are the typical ongoing costs for maintaining a professional business website?</summary>
              <div class="faq__answer"><p>After the initial build, the primary ongoing costs are hosting (typically $30–$100/month for high-quality, secure hosting) and your domain name (around $20/year). We also offer an optional Website Care Plan starting at $150/month, which includes daily backups, security monitoring, software updates, and minor content edits. This plan protects your investment and ensures your site remains fast, secure, and operational.</p></div>
            </details>
          </div>
          <div class="faq__group">
            <h3 class="faq__group-title">Process & Timelines</h3>
            <details class="faq__item">
              <summary class="faq__question">What is a realistic timeline for building a new website, from start to finish?</summary>
              <div class="faq__answer"><p>A realistic timeline for a new, custom service business website is 6 to 12 weeks. This breaks down into: Discovery & Strategy (1–2 weeks), Design & Copywriting (3–4 weeks), Development & SEO (3–4 weeks), and Testing & Launch (1–2 weeks). The timeline can be influenced by the project's complexity and the client's speed in providing feedback.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details class="faq__item">
              <summary class="faq__question">Can you describe the step-by-step process of a web design project?</summary>
              <div class="faq__answer"><p>Our process has three phases. Phase 1 — Strategy & Discovery: a 90-minute deep-dive call to understand your goals, audience, and competition, resulting in a detailed project blueprint. Phase 2 — Design & Development: we create wireframes and full-fidelity mockups for your approval, write the copy, and build on a private staging server. Phase 3 — Launch & Optimization: thorough QA, full migration and launch, then performance monitoring to ensure a smooth transition.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details class="faq__item">
              <summary class="faq__question">What specific information and materials do you need from me to begin?</summary>
              <div class="faq__answer"><p>To begin, the only thing we require is your participation in the initial 90-minute strategy session. During the project, we'll need any existing brand assets (logo in vector format, professional photography) and access to your domain registrar. We handle the rest, including all copywriting and stock image sourcing.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details class="faq__item">
              <summary class="faq__question">How much of my personal time will be required during the project?</summary>
              <div class="faq__answer"><p>We've engineered our process to minimize the time required from you. Expect approximately 2–3 hours for the initial strategy and discovery phase. After that, the commitment drops to about 30–60 minutes per week for providing feedback on designs and reviewing progress updates.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details class="faq__item">
              <summary class="faq__question">What kind of support is provided after the website is launched?</summary>
              <div class="faq__answer"><p>After launch, we provide 30 days of complimentary support to address any questions or minor issues. You'll also receive a comprehensive training video showing you how to manage your site's content. Following the initial 30 days, we offer ongoing Website Care Plans for continued support, updates, and security.</p></div>
            </details>
          </div>
          <div class="faq__group">
            <h3 class="faq__group-title">Results & ROI</h3>
            <details class="faq__item">
              <summary class="faq__question">How long does it take to see a measurable increase in leads from a new website?</summary>
              <div class="faq__answer"><p>While a new website provides an immediate boost in professionalism and credibility, measurable results like a significant increase in organic traffic and leads typically begin to appear within 3 to 6 months post-launch. This timeframe allows for Google to fully index the new site architecture and for our foundational SEO efforts to begin generating traction in search rankings.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details class="faq__item">
              <summary class="faq__question">What is a typical return on investment for a professionally designed website?</summary>
              <div class="faq__answer"><p>A typical ROI is realized when the cost of the website is offset by the profit from new business it generates. For many of our service business clients, this means closing just 1 to 3 new clients to achieve a full return on their investment. Our goal is for the website to pay for itself within the first year and become a consistent, profitable source of new business thereafter.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details class="faq__item">
              <summary class="faq__question">Which key performance indicators are most important for measuring a website's success?</summary>
              <div class="faq__answer"><p>We focus on KPIs tied directly to business growth: number of qualified leads (inquiries from ideal potential customers), conversion rate (percentage of visitors who take action), organic keyword rankings (visibility on Google for high-intent search terms), and cost per acquisition (effective cost to acquire a new lead through the website).</p></div>
            </details>
            <details class="faq__item">
              <summary class="faq__question">Can you provide specific examples or case studies of results you've achieved?</summary>
              <div class="faq__answer"><p>Yes. For example, we recently redesigned the website for a commercial roofing contractor. Within six months of launch, their organic traffic increased by 120%, and they were generating an average of 15 qualified quote requests per month, directly attributable to the new site. We're happy to share other relevant case studies during our initial consultation.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details class="faq__item">
              <summary class="faq__question">How exactly does a new website translate into more customer leads?</summary>
              <div class="faq__answer"><p>A new website translates into more leads through a three-part system. Attraction: it uses targeted SEO and content to attract high-intent visitors searching for your specific services. Trust: it builds credibility instantly with professional design, clear messaging, and social proof. Conversion: it guides visitors to take action with clear calls-to-action, simple forms, and a frictionless user experience.</p></div>
            </details>
          </div>
          <div class="faq__group">
            <h3 class="faq__group-title">Trust & Fit</h3>
            <details class="faq__item">
              <summary class="faq__question">What type of business is the ideal client for Lockard Design Co.?</summary>
              <div class="faq__answer"><p>The ideal client is an established service-based business with a proven track record that is ready to invest in a high-performance website to fuel its next stage of growth. Our process is best suited for owners who view their website as critical business infrastructure and a long-term asset, not just a line-item expense.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details class="faq__item">
              <summary class="faq__question">What is the advantage of working with a specialized founder-led company versus a large agency?</summary>
              <div class="faq__answer"><p>The primary advantage is direct access and accountability. When you work with Lockard Design Co., you work directly with the founder, Will Lockard. This ensures a deep understanding of your goals and a highly personalized level of service. Unlike large agencies where clients are often passed to junior account managers, our model provides a single point of contact dedicated entirely to your project's success.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details class="faq__item">
              <summary class="faq__question">Do you offer any kind of satisfaction or performance guarantee?</summary>
              <div class="faq__answer"><p>We offer a 100% Design Satisfaction Guarantee. This means we provide unlimited design revisions during the mockup phase of the project. We will continue to refine the design until you are completely happy with the look and feel, ensuring the final website is something you are proud of before we ever write a line of code.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details class="faq__item">
              <summary class="faq__question">What is your core philosophy that makes you different from other web designers?</summary>
              <div class="faq__answer"><p>Our core philosophy is that a website should be your #1 salesperson. This makes us different because we are not just designers — we are growth partners. While many designers focus solely on aesthetics, our entire process is built around a single goal: generating more qualified leads for your business. We measure our success by your business's growth, not just by how pretty the website looks.</p></div>
            </details>
            <details class="faq__item">
              <summary class="faq__question">Do you work with businesses located outside of your immediate geographic area?</summary>
              <div class="faq__answer"><p>Yes, approximately 70% of our clients are located outside of our immediate area. We are a remote-first company with a refined, seamless process for collaborating with businesses across the United States. Through video conferencing, project management software, and clear communication, we ensure a high-touch, personal experience regardless of your physical location.</p></div>
            </details>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

