      {"@type":"Question","name":"How long does it take to see a measurable increase in leads from a new website?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"While a new website provides an immediate boost in professionalism and credibility, measurable results like a significant increase in organic traffic and leads typically begin to appear within 3 to 6 months post-launch. This timeframe allows for Google to fully index the new site architecture and for our foundational SEO efforts to begin generating traction in search rankings."}},
      {"@type":"Question","name":"What is a typical return on investment for a professionally designed website?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A typical ROI is realized when the cost of the website is offset by the profit from new business it generates. For many of our service business clients, this means closing just 1 to 3 new clients to achieve a full return on their investment. Our goal is for the website to pay for itself within the first year and become a consistent, profitable source of new business thereafter."}},
      {"@type":"Question","name":"Which key performance indicators are most important for measuring a website's success?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"We focus on KPIs tied directly to business growth: number of qualified leads (inquiries from ideal potential customers), conversion rate (percentage of visitors who take action), organic keyword rankings (visibility on Google for high-intent search terms), and cost per acquisition (effective cost to acquire a new lead through the website)."}},
      {"@type":"Question","name":"Can you provide specific examples or case studies of results you've achieved?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. For example, we recently redesigned the website for a commercial roofing contractor. Within six months of launch, their organic traffic increased by 120%, and they were generating an average of 15 qualified quote requests per month, directly attributable to the new site. We're happy to share other relevant case studies during our initial consultation."}},
      {"@type":"Question","name":"How exactly does a new website translate into more customer leads?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A new website translates into more leads through a three-part system. Attraction: it uses targeted SEO and content to attract high-intent visitors searching for your specific services. Trust: it builds credibility instantly with professional design, clear messaging, and social proof. Conversion: it guides visitors to take action with clear calls-to-action, simple forms, and a frictionless user experience."}},
      {"@type":"Question","name":"What type of business is the ideal client for Lockard Design Co.?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The ideal client is an established service-based business with a proven track record that is ready to invest in a high-performance website to fuel its next stage of growth. Our process is best suited for owners who view their website as critical business infrastructure and a long-term asset, not just a line-item expense."}},
      {"@type":"Question","name":"What is the advantage of working with a specialized founder-led company versus a large agency?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The primary advantage is direct access and accountability. When you work with Lockard Design Co., you work directly with the founder, Will Lockard. This ensures a deep understanding of your goals and a highly personalized level of service. Unlike large agencies where clients are often passed to junior account managers, our model provides a single point of contact dedicated entirely to your project's success."}},
      {"@type":"Question","name":"Do you offer any kind of satisfaction or performance guarantee?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"We offer a 100% Design Satisfaction Guarantee. This means we provide unlimited design revisions during the mockup phase of the project. We will continue to refine the design until you are completely happy with the look and feel, ensuring the final website is something you are proud of before we ever write a line of code."}},
      {"@type":"Question","name":"What is your core philosophy that makes you different from other web designers?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Our core philosophy is that a website should be your #1 salesperson. This makes us different because we are not just designers — we are growth partners. While many designers focus solely on aesthetics, our entire process is built around a single goal: generating more qualified leads for your business. We measure our success by your business's growth, not just by how pretty the website looks."}},
      {"@type":"Question","name":"Do you work with businesses located outside of your immediate geographic area?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, approximately 70% of our clients are located outside of our immediate area. We are a remote-first company with a refined, seamless process for collaborating with businesses across the United States. Through video conferencing, project management software, and clear communication, we ensure a high-touch, personal experience regardless of your physical location."}}
    ]
  })} />


